com.team1389.motion_profile

Class SimpleKinematics

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.team1389.motion_profile.SimpleKinematics

  • public class SimpleKinematics
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a solved kinematics system with constant acceleration. It is final, in that once it is constructed each of the system's parameters will remain constant. To get any of the parameters one can access any of the final class variables.

    • Constructor Detail

      • SimpleKinematics

        public SimpleKinematics(double v0,
                        double vf,
                        double t,
                        double a,
                        double S)
        Creates and solves the kinematics system. At least three of the variable must be real, but the rest may be Double.NaN if they are unknown. No check is made to see if the motion is possible as described, and so invalid input may result in negative time or other unexpected results.
        Parameters:
        v0 - The initial velocity of the system
        vf - The final velocity of the system
        t - The total time the motion takes
        a - The constant acceleration of the system
        S - The distance traveled in the system
